              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "48-CD-116",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.025
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Targets were prepared by electroplating enriched 106Cd",
                "from alkaline cyanide solution onto 0.00025 in. gold",
                "foil. Cadmium deposits were uniform in thickness",
                "< 0.600 mg/cm2 to within 3%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two matched NaI(T1) crystals, each 2 mm thick",
                "by 1.5 in. in diameter, were used in almost 4Pi",
                "geometry. The effective solid angle subtended by a",
                "point source placed between two crystals was",
                "determined to be 98% of 4Pi."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "CHSEP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Anion exchange techniques were",
                "utilized in order to separate the tin, indium, and",
                "cadmium. For the isolation of silver and palladium,",
                "techniques involving precipitation of AgCl and",
                "palladiumdimethyl glyoxime were employed.",
                "Several targets were bombarded concurrently by means",
                "of the stacked-foil method. Each target was placed in",
                "the stack so that the gold foil intercepted the alpha",
                "beam before the Cd deposit. Aluminum foils, placed.",
                "behind the cadmium, served both to catch recoil nuclei",
                "and to degrade the energy of the beam. The range-energy",
                "relations of Bichsel for aluminum and gold were",
                "used to determine the energy of the alpha particles",
                "incident upon each cadmium target in the stack."
              ]
            }
          ],
